news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body collects record Rs 421 crore in property tax
news.para: This is the highest ever tax revenue realised by the Vizag civic body. By doing so, the GVMC surpassed its self-target of 375 crore tax collections for the 2023 fiscal.

news.title: At Rs 633 crore, Navi Mumbai civic body breaks its property tax collection record
news.para: By March 31, the civic body surpassed all previous year property tax collections and recorded Rs107.17 crore higher than last fiscal. The total collection of property tax in 2022-23 stood at Rs 633.17 crore against Rs 526 crore of the year 2021-22.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body's property tax collection up by 10%, but misses target again
news.para: However, overall property tax collection was more than last year by 10%. The civic body has assessed 13.53 lakh properties across the city, 7% more compared to 2021-22.

news.title: Patna civic body collects Rs 105 crore as property tax
news.para: Patna Municipal Corporation (PMC) has now planned to catch hold of such residential premises who have electricity connection but are not paying holding tax. It has also urged the residents to pay their taxes in the first three months for the current year and avail 5% rebate.

news.title: Civic body comes up with IDs of 5,000 new properties in Chandigarh
news.para: Since, matching of the records of electricity and estate office data with property tax is still going on, this number of 5,000 new properties will increase manifold in the coming days when the exercise is done by the MC.

news.title: Secunderabad cantonment board fails to hit property tax mark of Rs 30 crore this year
news.para: This fiscal year, SCB was expecting a target of 30 crore. According to SCB sources, there is no change in this year’s figure when compared with the last fiscal year’s collection.

news.title: Noida: 40% flats registered, 13% housing projects got completion certificates
news.para: Of these 115 projects with approved plans, 89 (77%) are defaulters and collectively owe Rs 26,000 crore in dues. Only 24 projects have paid all their dues while two have been cancelled.

news.title: Property owners in Nashik to get 5% rebate if facilities are set up
news.para: The five facilities comprise rainwater harvesting, EV charging stations, recycling of wastewater, solar water heaters and solar power panels.

news.title: Thousands protest in Portugal over housing crisis
news.para: Portugal is one of Western Europe's poorest countries, with government data showing more than 50% of workers earned less than 1,000 euros ($1,084) per month last year. The monthly minimum wage is 760 euros.

news.title: UltraTech Cement's production up 12.4% to 105.7 million tonnes in FY23
news.para: Its total sales volume in the domestic market also crossed 100 MT for the financial year that ended on March 31, 2023. UltraTech's total sales volume for the India market in FY23 was at 101.7 MT, up 13.63 per cent compared to 89.5 MT a year ago.

news.title: Bombay HC stays distribution of KDMC flats for the poor
news.para: The court order came while hearing a PIL filed by Kalyan-based architect Sandeep Patil who said those not eligible under the scheme have been included in eligible lists due to pressures from politicians.

news.title: Hyderabad: ED searches premises of Sahithi Infra, Phoenix group in real estate scam
news.para: ED also conducted searches on the offices of prominent real estate firm Phoenix group following the investigation, revealing significant land transactions between Sahithi. Searches were also conducted on Omics International.

news.title: Goa: Amendment cuts time for deemed building nod to 30 days in municipal areas
news.para: The bill stated that the existing period to issue construction permission is 60 days. It takes an additional 60 days if proper documents are not submitted. Also, permissions are being delayed in the office of the chief officer despite submission of all required documents, the bill stated.

news.title: Relax building norms for small plots in Kolkata: Mayor
news.para: The resident has been refused permission to build a house by the civic body’s buildings wing because the size of the plot made it difficult to adhere to mandatory open space that is required after construction.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires four acres land for residential project in Pune
news.para: The project will have a developable potential of approximately 7.5 lakh sq ft with an estimated revenue potential of approximately Rs 1,000 crore.
